        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-9" style="font-family: Source Sans Pro,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif">
          <h3>Dawn Murphy Redstone</h3>
          <h6>Champaign, IL</h6>
          <h6>Family Advocate</h6>
          <p>Dawn attended the University of South Florida and brings with her over ten years of law enforcement experience across Georgia and Florida. Dawn served both in road patrol and as a detective specializing in crimes against persons both young and old.  She began her healthcare career working in psychiatry as a Marketing Director in two local hospitals and went on to provide consultative services nationally to a number of small medical hospitals.  She spent seven years as a Patient Relations and HIPPA compliance Director for a local hospital system.  Her passion for helping seniors and their families more closely called her to change from a more corporate role to spending the next six years working in Assisted Living, Memory Care, and Skilled Nursing Facility sales and marketing. Upon learning about Soter Senior Living & Family Advocates and how we uniquely provide support to families in an unbiased manner she felt that this is where she belongs and gives her the best opportunity to utilize all of her experiences to “make a real difference.” She is dedicated and passionate about helping seniors and their families find the right resources, care options, or community to call their forever home.</p>
        </div>
